      "features": [
        {
          "name": "Rage",
          "desc": "Bonus action. +2 damage on STR attacks. Resistance to B/P/S damage. Advantage on STR checks and saves. Lasts 1 minute. 2 uses / long rest."
        },
        {
          "name": "Unarmored Defense",
          "desc": "AC = 10 + DEX mod (+2) + CON mod (+2) = 14 while not wearing armor."
        },
        {
          "name": "Daunting Roar (Leonin)",
          "desc": "Bonus action. Each creature of your choice within 10 ft must succeed on a WIS save (DC 12) or become frightened until the end of your next turn. 1/short rest."
        },
        {
          "name": "Darkvision (Leonin)",
          "desc": "See in dim light as if bright, and darkness as if dim light, within 60 feet."
        },
        {
          "name": "Wanderer (Outlander)",
          "desc": "Excellent memory for maps and terrain. Can find food and water for up to 5 companions per day in natural environments."
        }
      ],
      "traits": {
        "personality": "He watches over companions as if they were a litter of newborn cubs. He does not show it openly — but he positions himself between danger and the weak without thinking.",
        "ideal": "Glory is remembrance. To be remembered is to resist erasure. Every battle must mean something — his name must echo in story long after his bones bleach in the sand.",
        "bond": "He walks so the memory of the First Land does not die. The weight of a fallen pride lives in every step.",
        "flaw": "He is slow to trust outsiders. Respect must be earned in sweat and blood. You do not simply enter a pride by standing near it."
      },
      "equipment": [
        "Sun-Disc Club (Greatclub)",
        "Explorer's Pack",
        "Hunting Trap",
        "First-Land Stone Fragment",
        "Traveler's Clothes",
        "Gold Ceremonial Arm Cuff",
        "Desert Drum",
        "Belt Pouch"
      ],
      "gold": 10,
      "rage": {
        "uses": 2,
        "damage_bonus": 2,
        "resistances": "B/P/S"
      },
      "backstory": {
        "short": "Before the Temporal Compression, his homeland breathed with mythic air. The horizon was wider. Spirits walked the surface of things. Then the world hardened. Matter thickened. What moved like wind became stone-bound. His pride faded — some into legend, some into the petrified ruins that scholars now mistake for ancient monuments. He held form. Not because he was strongest — but because his will refused to dissolve.",
        "chapters": [
          {
            "title": "The First Land",
            "subtitle": "Before the Compression",
            "text": "Long ago, his homeland was not like the world is now. The air was lighter. The horizon wider. Creatures moved as song. Spirits walked at the surface of things. There was no barrier between the mythic and the physical — they were the same substance, breathing together."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Temporal Compression",
            "subtitle": "The Fall",
            "text": "Then came the shift — not a war, not a disaster. A hardening. The world compressed. Matter thickened. What once moved like wind became stone-bound. What once sang in the air fell silent. His pride did not all survive the transition. Some faded. Some became legend. Some petrified into monuments that scholars now mistake for ancient ruins."
          },
          {
            "title": "He Held Form",
            "subtitle": "Why He Survived",
            "text": "He endured — not because he was strongest, but because his will would not dissolve. His rage anchored him to reality when reality itself was rewriting. He carries oral history that no book records. He remembers things that, to the modern world, never happened."
          },
          {
            "title": "A World Too Small",
            "subtitle": "Now",
            "text": "Now he walks a world that feels smaller than it should be. He recognizes shapes in ruins others don't. He sometimes stares at stone and sees motion. He treats mountains like former living things. He does not rant. He is steady. Grounded. A survivor of the hardening of the world."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Core Question",
            "subtitle": "What drives him",
            "text": "Does he believe the world fell once and it is done — or that the world is still falling, just slowly enough that no one else can feel it? That answer determines how he rages. And what he's really fighting for."
          }
        ]
      },
