      "traits": {
        "personality": "Small in stature, enormous in presence. Her curiosity is insatiable — she will touch everything, ask about everything, remember everything. Her laughter is genuine; her silences are calculating.",
        "ideal": "Knowledge without application is just hoarding. She studies the boundary between life and death not out of morbidity, but because she believes something important lives there.",
        "bond": "Her spellbook contains pressed flowers, margin notes in three languages, and a spell she hasn't been able to cast yet. The people she travels with have become, unexpectedly, something she would cross swamps for.",
        "flaw": "She occasionally forgets other people cannot fly, hide instantly, or talk to mushrooms — leading to plans that only work if you're her."
      },
