      "backstory": {
        "summary": "A lowly intern. Evo saw a job ad for Moogle, a Fortune 5000 company, and got hired on the spot — but misread the description. They didn't want a cleric; they wanted a clerk. He spent his time in the archives learning their secrets, and now aims to undercut them by starting his own information company: Duck Duck Dragon. He joined a random party to get startup funds.",
        "full": "A lowly intern who stumbled into the wrong career and decided to own it. Evo applied to Moogle, misread the job description, and arrived as a Cleric when they wanted a clerk. The mockery was immediate. Rather than quit, he spent every spare hour in the company archives, memorizing partner lists, contracts, and leverage. When he finally walked out, he had a plan: Duck Duck Dragon, his own information brokerage. He joined an adventuring party for seed money."
      }
